01:22:45,507 --> 01:22:47,099
Ode, four, three.

1181
01:22:49,311 --> 01:22:51,541
l love you, Mom.

1182
01:22:51,713 --> 01:22:53,510
l will always love you.

1183
01:22:54,783 --> 01:22:58,685
l'm sorry,
but l would rather live with Gracie.

1184
01:23:01,490 --> 01:23:03,014
What?

1185
01:23:06,561 --> 01:23:09,792
Well, he's been brainwashed.
Wait, wait, wait.

1186
01:23:09,965 --> 01:23:13,958
-Jonny, what about you?
-Jonny. Jon, Jon, Jon. Now, look at me.

1187
01:23:14,136 --> 01:23:16,468
-Miss Larson!
-Look at your mother.

1188
01:23:17,773 --> 01:23:20,241
Clearly, she has-- She's--

1189
01:23:20,409 --> 01:23:24,277
She's poisoned them or brainwashed them
to be scared of me...

1190
01:23:24,446 --> 01:23:28,041
-Counsel, l've warned you.
-...and told them that l am bad.

1191
01:23:30,118 --> 01:23:34,214
l'm not bad. l'm not bad.
l'm just looking for another chance.

1192
01:23:35,724 --> 01:23:39,990
One more chance, please, to be
their mother. Boys, come to me.

1193
01:23:40,162 --> 01:23:41,993
Jonny...

1194
01:23:42,331 --> 01:23:43,764
...come to me, my babies.

1195
01:23:45,500 --> 01:23:46,933
Boys.

1196
01:23:47,102 --> 01:23:50,162
Boys, l know this is going
to be very difficult...

1197
01:23:50,339 --> 01:23:52,830
...but ignore what your mother
just said to you.

1198
01:23:53,141 --> 01:23:56,042
Just try and stay with your feelings.

1199
01:23:57,045 --> 01:23:58,808
Jonny...

1200
01:23:59,114 --> 01:24:00,877
...who do you want to live with?

1201
01:24:02,417 --> 01:24:06,285
Your Honor, we've been with Gracie
all our lives.

1202
01:24:06,455 --> 01:24:10,289
She feeds us and reads to us...

1203
01:24:10,459 --> 01:24:13,724
...and helps us with our lessons.

1204
01:24:14,429 --> 01:24:19,594
She fixes us up when we're hurt
and when we're scared.

1205
01:24:19,768 --> 01:24:22,430
That's what a mother does, right?

1206
01:24:22,604 --> 01:24:25,539
She changed our diapers
when we were babies.

1207
01:24:26,308 --> 01:24:29,175
-Mom, you know that's true.
-Robbie?

1208
01:24:30,078 --> 01:24:32,512
Robbie, what do you say about this?

1209
01:24:32,681 --> 01:24:36,742
Robbie, pay attention.
Who do you want to live with?

1210
01:24:36,918 --> 01:24:40,217
l would like to live in Wyoming
and ride a horse.

1211
01:24:41,289 --> 01:24:43,849
-Wyoming?
-Yeah, it would be fun.

1212
01:24:44,359 --> 01:24:46,088
Yeah, yeah.

1213
01:24:46,261 --> 01:24:51,358
But l would like to sleep in my own bed
and go home with Gracie.

1214
01:25:00,675 --> 01:25:03,075
l can take care of it.

1215
01:25:05,914 --> 01:25:09,645
l've been with this case
for some time now.

1216
01:25:09,985 --> 01:25:15,252
lt seems the children
have finally found some stability.

1217
01:25:15,957 --> 01:25:18,187
l don't want to disrupt that.

1218
01:25:18,360 --> 01:25:22,729
Miss Larson, l know you feel
pain and remorse...

1219
01:25:22,898 --> 01:25:25,765
...but it's all coming too late.

1220
01:25:27,502 --> 01:25:29,697
Parental rights are terminated.

1221
01:25:37,078 --> 01:25:41,378
ls that--? ls that it?

1222
01:25:48,190 --> 01:25:51,557
l can't see my babies anymore?

1223
01:25:55,764 --> 01:25:58,858
You're not my babies anymore?

1224
01:25:59,534 --> 01:26:01,764
Oh, God!

1225
01:26:10,679 --> 01:26:13,876
l love you, my boys. l love you.

1226
01:26:16,485 --> 01:26:21,149
l will always find you.
No matter where you go, l will find you.

1227
01:26:44,112 --> 01:26:46,637
l hope you know
what you're doing today.

1228
01:26:46,815 --> 01:26:49,249
This is a huge thing you're taking on.

1229
01:26:49,417 --> 01:26:53,353
There's no turning back.
These will be your children now.

1230
01:26:53,522 --> 01:26:55,649
l understand.

1231
01:26:55,824 --> 01:26:57,724
They've always been my children.

1232
01:26:58,126 --> 01:27:00,924
They've never been anyone else's.

1233
01:27:01,596 --> 01:27:03,757
Now, can we blow this joint?

1234
01:27:07,769 --> 01:27:11,034
-He means, are we done?
-Almost.

1235
01:27:11,473 --> 01:27:13,873
-Diesel, like Vin Diesel.
-That's stupid.

1236
01:27:14,042 --> 01:27:16,567
-Potter, like Harry.
-Guys, we gotta get serious.

1237
01:27:16,745 --> 01:27:19,270
We have five minutes
to come up with a last name.

1238
01:27:19,447 --> 01:27:21,779
-Lobo.
-That's the cat's name.

1239
01:27:21,950 --> 01:27:23,815
Savage.

1240
01:27:24,386 --> 01:27:26,081
Jonny Savage.

1241
01:27:26,254 --> 01:27:30,122
No, how about Weatherly?

1242
01:27:32,093 --> 01:27:34,425
Because we've been through
bad weather.

1243
01:27:34,596 --> 01:27:37,929
-Weatherly. Jonny Weatherly. Okay.
-Okay with me.

1244
01:27:38,099 --> 01:27:39,657
All right, Weatherly.

1245
01:27:42,971 --> 01:27:45,132
Weatherly, Your Honor.

1246
01:27:48,877 --> 01:27:51,812
Ladies and gentlemen of the courtroom,
for the record...

1247
01:27:51,980 --> 01:27:54,608
...l'm happy to present
the Weatherly family.

1248
01:27:54,783 --> 01:27:56,546
-Yes.
-Yes.

1249
01:27:56,718 --> 01:27:58,185
Gracie Weatherly...

1250
01:27:58,353 --> 01:27:59,980
...Ryan Weatherly...

1251
01:28:00,155 --> 01:28:02,487
-...Jonny Weatherly...
-Yes!

1252
01:28:02,657 --> 01:28:04,352
...and Robbie Weatherly.

1253
01:28:04,526 --> 01:28:07,393
This is a miracle. lt's a first.

1254
01:28:07,562 --> 01:28:10,895
l want to see you guys
when you graduate.

1255
01:28:11,066 --> 01:28:13,557
lt's heroic what you're doing.

1256
01:28:13,735 --> 01:28:18,263
l wondered, when l was
reading the case...

1257
01:28:18,440 --> 01:28:22,536
...if l'd make a mistake by granting this.

1258
01:28:23,445 --> 01:28:27,040
But l know in my heart
l've made the right decision.

1259
01:28:28,617 --> 01:28:33,850
-l just hope you can handle it.
-l will. l can do it.

1260
01:28:34,022 --> 01:28:36,013
lt's gonna be hard.

1261
01:28:36,491 --> 01:28:39,551
You've got your own little family now.

1262
01:28:39,728 --> 01:28:42,458
You can make it happen.

1263
01:29:06,721 --> 01:29:10,680
We are proud to present the Weatherlys!

1264
01:30:17,625 --> 01:30:19,616
[ENGLlSH]

